d (line 2445): Uses validate_slug or validate_unicode_slug\n- GenericIPAddressField (line 2254): Uses ip_address_validators based on protocol\n- IntegerField (line 2099): Dynamically adds MinValueValidator and MaxValueValidator based on database field range\n- DecimalField (line 1698): Uses DecimalValidator for precision validation\n\n**4. Specialized Field Validation**\n- ForeignKey.validate() (django/db/models/fields/related.py, line 1211): Validates that referenced foreign key values exist\n- JSONField.validate() (django/db/models/fields/json.py, line 129): Ensures JSON serializability\n- AutoFieldMixin.validate() (django/db/models/fields/__init__.py, line 2852): Override for auto-fields\n\n**5. Contrib Validators**\n- django/contrib/auth/validators.py: ASCIIUsernameValidator and UnicodeUsernameValidator for Django auth\n- django/contrib/postgres/validators.py: PostgreSQL-specific validators including ArrayMaxLengthValidator, ArrayMinLengthValidator, KeysValidator, RangeMaxValueValidator, and RangeMinValueValidator\n\nThe validation chain ensures: user input is type-converted (to_python), field-specific validation runs (validate), registered validators execute (run_validators), and finally model-level validation occurs (clean) before database operations."
