  "text": "Django's model field validation coverage is implemented across multiple files forming a comprehensive validation pipeline. The core validation system is built on three main layers:\n\n**1. Validator Functions and Classes (django/core/validators.py)**\nThe foundation consists of built-in validator classes: MaxLengthValidator (line 489), MinValueValidator (line 424), MaxValueValidator (line 415), EmailValidator (line 210), and URLValidator (line 130). Supporting validators include DecimalValidator (line 507) for decimal precision validation, FileExtensionValidator (line 595), ProhibitNullCharactersValidator (line 656), and others. Helper validator functions include validate_email, validate_slug, validate_unicode_slug, validate_ipv4_address, validate_ipv6_address, validate_ipv46_address, validate_integer, validate_comma_separated_integer_list, and validate_image_file_extension.\n\n**2. Model-Level Validation Pipeline (django/db/models/base.py)**\nThe validation pipeline starts with Model.full_clean() (line 1690), which orchestrates the complete validation process. It calls clean_fields() (line 1737) to validate all fields, clean() (line 1440) for custom model validation, validate_unique() (line 1450) for uniqueness constraints, and validate_constraints() (line 1670) for database constraints.\n\n**3. Field-Level Validation (django/db/models/fields/__init__.py)**\nEach field implements three key validation methods:\n- Field.validate() (line 798): Validates field-specific rules (choices, null/blank requirements)\n- Field.clean() (line 829): Converts value type and runs all validation\n- Field.run_validators() (line 782): Applies registered validator functions\n\nSpecific field classes integrate validators as default_validators:\n- CharField (line 1204) and BinaryField (line 2702): Add MaxLengthValidator for max_length\n- EmailField (line 1955): Uses validate_email as default validator\n- URLField (line 2677): Uses URLValidator() as default validator\n- SlugField (line 2445): Uses validate_slug or validate_unicode_slug\n- GenericIPAddressField (line 2254): Uses ip_address_validators based on protocol\n- IntegerField (line 2099): Dynamically adds MinValueValidator and MaxValueValidator based on database field range\n- DecimalField (line 1698): Uses DecimalValidator for precision validation\n\n**4. Specialized Field Validation**\n- ForeignKey.validate() (django/db/models/fields/related.py, line 1211): Validates that referenced foreign key values exist\n- JSONField.validate() (django/db/models/fields/json.py, line 129): Ensures JSON serializability\n- AutoFieldMixin.validate() (django/db/models/fields/__init__.py, line 2852): Override for auto-fields\n\n**5. Contrib Validators**\n- django/contrib/auth/validators.py: ASCIIUsernameValidator and UnicodeUsernameValidator for Django auth\n- django/contrib/postgres/validators.py: PostgreSQL-specific validators including ArrayMaxLengthValidator, ArrayMinLengthValidator, KeysValidator, RangeMaxValueValidator, and RangeMinValueValidator\n\nThe validation chain ensures: user input is type-converted (to_python), field-specific validation runs (validate), registered validators execute (run_validators), and finally model-level validation occurs (clean) before database operations."
